<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-558-862  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 558 862.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  June 18 1990 v7 n24 p34(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software Publishing adds PFS:Preface to product line designed forbeginners. (DOS enhancing program) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Software Publishing Corp. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    SPCO.andO;Product:   PFS:Preface (Operating system enhancement) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionMenusUser AidsFile ManagementUtility ProgramsAdd-In-On Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Software Publishing Corp. will expand its line of software designed fornovice users this month with the shipment of PFS:Preface, a menu system andDOS utility.andM;During its install routine, the $69 PFS:Preface utility automatically createsa menu system of applications located on the user's hard-disk drive.andP;  A usercan customize the order and contents of this menu.andM;Once the menu is set up, an application is loaded with a single keystroke.andM;PFS:Preface simplifies basic DOS functions through the use of pull-down menusand file displays, according to officials of Software Publishing, which islocated in Mountain View, Calif.andM;Users can also search for files across a hard-disk drive through a file nameor wild-card command.andM;Tasks such as copying, deleting, renaming, moving and viewing files can alsobe performed from within the file-manager function in PFS:Preface.andP;  These DOSfunctions can be performed on several files and directories at the same time.andM;PFS:Preface also features a DOS window that allows users to execute DOScommands without leaving the program.andP;  The DOS window includes an on-lineguide to DOS with definitions and examples of its features.andM;System requirements include a computer running DOS 2.1 or higher, a hard diskand 512K bytes of RAM.andM;Software Publishing Corp. can be reached at (415) 962-8910.andO;</TEXT></DOC>